      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(channels): add directUserId support for per-DM model override",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\n`channels.modelByChannel` could select provider/model overrides for group conversations (`-100123`) and wildcard (`*`), but not for individual DM peers. Operators had no way to pin different models per user in direct messages.\n\n## Changes\n\n### Core: `src/channels/model-overrides.ts`\n- **`directUserId` → `directUserIds` array**: Callers now pass all available identity fields as an array; the resolver tries each one until a key match is found.\n- **`expandPeerIds`**: When a candidate has a `<channel>:` prefix (e.g. `telegram:12345`), the resolver also tries the unprefixed form (`12345`), so stored-session paths that only persist channel-prefixed IDs can match raw config keys.\n- **Direct-chat gate**: `resolveDirectChannelModelMatch` only runs when `normalizeChatType(params.groupChatType) === \"direct\"`, preventing DM key leakage into group/channel messages.\n\n### Callers\n| File | What changed |\n|------|-------------|\n| `get-reply.ts` | Live reply path — passes all 6 identity fields from stored session + finalized context |\n| `dispatch-from-config.ts` | Same as get-reply |\n| `status-message.ts` | Stored-session path — passes origin fields (prefixes expanded by `expandPeerIds`) |\n| `agent-command.ts` | Stored-session path — same approach |\n\n### Docs\n- `docs/gateway/config-channels.md`: DM key-forms table for all major channels\n- `src/config/schema.help.ts`: Help text updated to \"channel id / DM peer id\"\n- `src/config/types.channels.ts`: JSDoc updated\n\n## Evidence\n\n### Live Feishu DM test\n\nGateway config using `modelByChannel` with Feishu DM override:\n```\nfeishu:\n  \"feishu:ou_a8b6cab7e945387de5f253775d9b4d85\": tencent/kimi-k2.5\n  \"*\": tencent/glm-5\n```\n\nGateway log confirms DM peer override selected:\n```\nmodel=kimi-k2.5  ← from feishu DM specific entry, not wildcard glm-5\n```\n\nConfig channel: `feishu`\nUser ID format: `feishu:ou_...` (with channel prefix)\nDefault wildcard model: `glm-5`\n\nSee PR comment with before/after gateway log output.\n\n## Tests\n\n### `model-overrides.test.ts` — 19 tests\n\n| Category | Tests | What it covers |\n|----------|-------|---------------|\n| Group/parent matching | 4 | groupId, topic suffix, parent session key, channel name fallback |\n| Plugin conversation | 2 | plugin-owned conversation resolution |\n| Wildcard direct | 1 | `*` works for direct chats |\n| DM matching (single) | 5 | directUserId match, wildcard fallback, origin.from match, group precedence, non-direct gating |\n| DM matching (multi-candidate) | 4 | Slack/Discord/Telegram channel-specific forms, candidate priority |\n| Prefix expansion | 3 | telegram/discord prefix stripping, cross-channel non-match |\n\n### Agent-command live-model-switch — 65 tests (all passing)\n### Slack extension prepare — 85 tests (all passing)\n",
        "branch": "fix/issue-53638-per-channel-model-override",
